# =============================================================================
# .gitignore — what NOT to track in d-os.
#
# Goal: a clean checkout has only sources, build scripts, and docs.  Everything
# the build / dev workflow generates lives in /build/ and stays out of git.
#
# When adding a new ignore: prefer a pattern that's narrow (e.g. only the file
# extensions actually produced) over a blanket directory ignore that could
# accidentally hide a real source file.
# =============================================================================

# --- Build outputs --------------------------------------------------------
# Everything the Makefile + Docker emit lands here.  Includes kernel.bin,
# d-os.iso, and the iso/ staging tree.
/build/

# Object files emitted next to .c sources by the in-tree compile rule.
# Match anywhere (e.g. kernel/core/foo.o, kernel/hal/x86/io.o).
*.o

# Final binary / ISO / debug artifacts at any depth — defensive, in case
# someone drops one outside /build/ during ad-hoc work.
*.bin
*.iso
*.elf
*.map
*.lst

# --- Editor / OS noise ----------------------------------------------------
# macOS Finder metadata, recursive.
.DS_Store
**/.DS_Store

# Vim swap files.
*.sw[ponm]
*~

# Emacs autosave / backup.
*#
.\#*

# JetBrains, VS Code, Sublime, Xcode local config.
.idea/
.vscode/
*.sublime-workspace
*.sublime-project
*.xcodeproj/
*.xcuserdatad/

# Claude Code local settings (per-machine permission allowlist).
.claude/

# --- Local debug / test artifacts ----------------------------------------
# Files our smoke-test scripts and pmemsave tricks dump locally.  They live
# under /tmp normally but a developer occasionally lands them at the repo
# root by mistake.
*.log
serial.log
qemu.log
vga.bin
fb.bin
mbi.bin
test.img
disk.img

# Vendored (fetched, pristine) musl source — see scripts/fetch-musl.sh
third_party/musl/
# Built static i386 musl (make musl) — a build product, rebuilt on demand
third_party/musl-i386/
# musl-linked ELFs (build products)
user/*.muslelf
# §M37 dynamic-linking build products (PIE ELFs + shared objects)
user/*.dynelf
user/*.so
# §M38 musl C++ cross-toolchain (build input + product)
third_party/musl-cross-make/
third_party/musl-cross-*/
# §M39 Mbed TLS (vendored crypto dep + build product)
third_party/mbedtls/
third_party/mbedtls-i686/
# §M38 C++ build products
user/*.cxxelf
# §M43 TinyCC (on-device C compiler — vendored build input + product)
third_party/tinycc/
third_party/tinycc-i686/
# §M43 on-device compiler build products
user/rootfs.bin
user/dostcc
